### Important notes
- The static layout has access to `HttpContext` because it renders via SSR on every navigation
- Interactive pages capture the session ID from `IHttpContextAccessor` during their prerender/init phase
- The singleton `WizardStateStore` survives across circuit disposals, so data persists when navigating between wizard steps
- Each user gets their own session cookie, so wizard data is isolated per-user
- `AddHttpContextAccessor()` is required in Program.cs

After creating all files, run `dotnet build` to verify everything compiles.

